(SHAKES COINS)

66
00:08:02,695 --> 00:08:04,662
Our agreed-upon sum.

67
00:08:05,828 --> 00:08:07,463
- Sir, very good.
- Very good indeed.

68
00:08:07,497 --> 00:08:08,965
- Hmm.
- In fact,

69
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,366
I would like to
treble the order.

70
00:08:11,734 --> 00:08:13,233
Three times the order?

71
00:08:13,267 --> 00:08:15,836
- Three crates instead of one?
- Yes.

72
00:08:17,305 --> 00:08:18,337
In that case...

73
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:20,137
Is there a problem?

74
00:08:20,171 --> 00:08:21,305
No, no. No.

75
00:08:21,673 --> 00:08:22,874
(CHUCKLES)

76
00:08:22,908 --> 00:08:25,941
But you have purchased
so much from me by now.

77
00:08:26,409 --> 00:08:30,914
Allow me to ask, what is the
purpose for so much rice?

78
00:08:31,315 --> 00:08:36,056
Oh, well, I do not see where
that is your concern, Mr. Chang.

79
00:08:36,090 --> 00:08:40,529
Only that, if someone were to become
aware of the business we do together,

80
00:08:40,563 --> 00:08:42,132
if there was any trouble...

81
00:08:42,166 --> 00:08:45,169
That will not happen.

82
00:08:47,002 --> 00:08:51,706
But if you wish, I'm sure I can acquire
another source of supply in the future.

83
00:08:53,810 --> 00:08:57,344
I will do so.
Good day, Mr. Chang.

84
00:08:58,647 --> 00:09:01,048
It's not necessary,
Mr. Gundersen.

85
00:09:01,315 --> 00:09:04,520
Perhaps,
it was just my curiosity.

86
00:09:04,555 --> 00:09:06,952
Three crates,
the 10th of next month.

87
00:09:06,987 --> 00:09:13,626
Although I must ask for another $20
per crate, due to costs and risks.

88
00:09:15,527 --> 00:09:16,593
$10.

89
00:09:18,066 --> 00:09:19,634
(LAUGHS)

90
00:09:21,871 --> 00:09:22,971
$10.

91
00:09:24,139 --> 00:09:25,672
- (CLICKS TONGUE)
- (CRACKS REINS)

92
00:09:34,316 --> 00:09:35,450
TAO: All is ready.

93
00:09:35,484 --> 00:09:37,354
CULLEN: All right. Matches.

94
00:09:39,456 --> 00:09:40,521
Tao.

95
00:09:45,928 --> 00:09:47,261
Say your piece.

96
00:09:48,295 --> 00:09:49,795
You forbid Mei to work.

97
00:09:50,096 --> 00:09:52,098
No women on the railroad,
plain and simple.

98
00:09:52,132 --> 00:09:54,402
The men will ask questions.

99
00:09:54,838 --> 00:09:57,040
I'll keep a tight lip, but
that's as far as I go with this.

100
00:09:57,075 --> 00:09:58,509
Now light the damn fuse.

101
00:09:58,544 --> 00:10:01,713
She does good work.
She works like a man.

102
00:10:01,915 --> 00:10:02,949
Nope.

103
00:10:02,983 --> 00:10:05,582
- She is better than two men...
- No, I said.

104
00:10:07,184 --> 00:10:10,923
If Mei does not work,
the men wonder why.

105
00:10:11,458 --> 00:10:13,059
Not safe for her.

106
00:10:14,227 --> 00:10:18,030
You let her work or I
take her away from here.

107
00:10:18,867 --> 00:10:20,302
(SCOFFS)

108
00:10:20,336 --> 00:10:21,637
And go where?

109
00:10:22,338 --> 00:10:26,407
We have left everything
behind already.

110
00:10:27,974 --> 00:10:29,641
Much more than this.

111
00:10:29,676 --> 00:10:31,646
JENKINS: Bohannon!
What's the hold-up?

112
00:10:31,681 --> 00:10:33,451
Calm the hell down.

113
