second, by imitation..."

245
00:18:57,305 --> 00:18:58,970
"And third, by experience."

246
00:18:59,538 --> 00:19:01,172
- "Which is the bitterest."
- Hmm.

247
00:19:01,207 --> 00:19:07,044
Wisdom gained through experience is the
reason young men must respect their elders.

248
00:19:09,347 --> 00:19:12,349
You are right, Ah-Tao, forgive me.

249
00:19:13,351 --> 00:19:14,352
Lili! (SPEAKS CANTONESE)

250
00:19:19,689 --> 00:19:22,525
Lili is one of our most experienced girls.

251
00:19:23,195 --> 00:19:25,931
Imagine the wisdom she could provide.

252
00:19:26,733 --> 00:19:29,901
A free night for you, out of respect.

253
00:19:32,930 --> 00:19:34,639
_

254
00:19:49,458 --> 00:19:50,724
(SPEAKS CANTONESE)

255
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:53,308
(DOOR CLOSES)

256
00:20:01,633 --> 00:20:05,633
Now I told you not to fool with that.
Give me here.

257
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:10,742
(SIGHS)

258
00:20:10,776 --> 00:20:13,516
Run along, go wash up for dinner, Janie.

259
00:20:18,223 --> 00:20:20,692
I just didn't want her to
prick her finger, is all.

260
00:20:22,529 --> 00:20:24,530
- Listen.
- (SIGHING)

261
00:20:26,332 --> 00:20:27,732
(HANNA CHUCKLES)

262
00:20:27,766 --> 00:20:30,605
Whatever it is, you'll find a way through.

263
00:20:31,941 --> 00:20:33,441
You always do, James.

264
00:20:41,952 --> 00:20:43,354
Mr. Bohannon.

265
00:20:46,857 --> 00:20:48,258
Aren't you going to ask
your boss to sit down?

266
00:20:52,228 --> 00:20:54,596
HANNA: Perhaps I'll fix you two
some dinner, it's nearly time.

267
00:20:54,630 --> 00:20:57,329
I was gonna take Jim away
from here, get us a drink.

268
00:21:04,571 --> 00:21:06,304
(JAMES SIGHS)

269
00:21:10,079 --> 00:21:12,415
I'm used to you running your mouth.

270
00:21:15,951 --> 00:21:18,119
You might not like what I gotta say.

271
00:21:20,222 --> 00:21:21,890
(SIGHS) Damn it.

272
00:21:24,227 --> 00:21:26,398
You cut me down today with my men.

273
00:21:27,283 --> 00:21:28,917
Clean gelded me.

274
00:21:30,838 --> 00:21:32,907
Implies you had a pair to begin with.

275
00:21:35,177 --> 00:21:36,345
I had it under control.

276
00:21:37,546 --> 00:21:40,478
- Hell you did.
- It was moving in the right direction.

277
00:21:41,180 --> 00:21:42,947
(CLINKS GLASS)

278
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:44,414
Hell it was.

279
00:21:54,257 --> 00:21:56,755
Ask nice, Johnny Reb.

280
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:00,495
I ain't asking.

281
00:22:17,620 --> 00:22:19,421
Tread light, son.

282
00:22:22,022 --> 00:22:23,221
You got this?

283
00:22:27,562 --> 00:22:28,794
(SCOFFS)

284
00:22:38,585 --> 00:22:40,786
(INDISTINCT CHATTER IN CANTONESE)

285
00:22:43,190 --> 00:22:44,891
(MIC PLAYING)

286
00:24:07,267 --> 00:24:09,487
They're takin' money from our pockets,

287
00:24:09,490 --> 00:24:12,643
food from our bellies and
roofs from over our heads.

288
00:24:13,443 --> 00:24:15,147
They come over here and do they

289
00:24:15,150 --> 00:24:17,347
even bother to learn our language? No.

290
00:24:17,915 --> 00:24:21,888
Do they live like normal people should? No.

291
00:24:22,823 --> 00:24:26,357
They don't contribute a goddamn thing.

292
00:24:26,860 --> 00:24:28,528
They just take.

293
00:24:28,562 --> 00:24:31,200
They can afford to work for nothing, sure,

294
00:24:31,235 --> 00:24:32,900
when they're willing to eat rats and worms.

295
00:24:32,934 --> 00:24:34,833
Listen to me now, boys.

296
00:24:34,867 --> 00:24:38,870
I have no love for the
Chinaman, but they work hard.

297
00:24:39,238 --> 00:24:41,407
We've all seen it. You only gotta
show 'em a thing but once,

298
00:24:41,441 --> 00:24:43,410
and they do it as good as any white man.

299
00:24:43,445 --> 00:24:45,813
They keep to themselves
and they don't complain.

300
00:24:45,847 --> 00:24:48,716
Belly-achin' ain't gonna send
the yellow man back to China.

301
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:52,521
Them slant eyes need to be taught
a lesson's what they need.

302
00:24:53,657 --> 00:24:55,293
That's enough.

303
00:24:58,965 --> 00:25:01,967
I gave you a chance. I
said I'd look out for you.

304
00:25:02,001 --> 00:25:04,235
It's more than I gave
any one of them Jakes.

305
00:25:04,970 --> 00:25:07,707
Now I'm goin' home to my family.

306
00:25:08,575 --> 00:25:10,578
I think you should turn in, too.

307
00:25:10,612 --> 00:25:12,147
Think about this fresh tomorrow.

308
00:25:13,550 --> 00:25:15,715
PETE: We ain't working
for you no more, Stro.

309
00:25:16,517 --> 00:25:18,182
You don't tell us what to do.

310
00:25:18,216 --> 00:25:20,953
No, no, no, boys. He's right.

311
00:25:22,423 --> 00:25:24,054
There's no good we can do.

312
00:25:26,859 --> 00:25:29,157
We'll finish up our drinks and then...

313
00:25:50,079 --> 00:25:53,684
I wanna talk about this once and
put it behind for good. All right?

314
00:26:00,461 --> 00:26:01,828
(MEI SIGHS)

315
00:26:05,163 --> 00:26:06,463
If I no work...

316
00:26:06,497 --> 00:26:08,665
You're in danger. I get it.

317
00:26:13,105 --> 00:26:17,240
When rebel burn our village, Taiping war,

318
00:26:18,243 --> 00:26:20,177
they take all women.

319
00:26:22,281 --> 00:26:26,884
Rebel leader, he choose me for...
For his bride.

320
00:26:29,157 --> 00:26:32,325
Rebel leader, he Sze Yup Company now.

321
00:26:33,628 --> 00:26:36,267
Many workers here Sze Yup Company.

322
00:26:37,603 --> 00:26:40,740
Chang, is he Sze Yup?

323
00:26:46,814 --> 00:26:50,251
Chang work for rebel
leader in San Francisco.

324
00:26:51,653 --> 00:26:52,819
(SIGHS)

325
00:26:52,854 --> 00:26:57,757
If Sze Yup find me, make me
Daughter of Sun and Moon.

326
00:26:59,928 --> 00:27:01,161
(SIGHS)

327
00:27:03,665 --> 00:27:05,901
I belong to them.

328
00:27:06,536 --> 00:27:08,270
That's why I hide.

329
00:27:09,273 --> 00:27:12,176
This is America. Ain't
nobody belongs to nobody.

330
00:27:12,211 --> 00:27:13,611
We fought a war over it.

331
00:27:13,911 --> 00:27:15,144
(SCOFFS)

332
00:27:16,146 --> 00:27:17,982
But we still Chinese.

333
00:27:23,222 --> 00:27:24,688
(SIGHS)

334
00:27:34,932 --> 00:27:35,933
Tomorrow morning.

335
00:27:39,403 --> 00:27:41,238
Eight o'clock sharp.

336
00:27:43,275 --> 00:27:45,908
I need all the good men I can get.

337
00:27:46,910 --> 00:27:48,478
Fong included.

338
00:27:52,616 --> 00:27:53,949
(SIGHS)

339
00:27:56,216 --> 00:27:57,550
(CHUCKLES)

340
00:27:57,885 --> 00:28:00,087
CHEN: Welcome. Can I help you gentlemen?

341
00:28:00,122 --> 00:28:02,958
MATT: Yeah, we want what
you got, China Jake.

342
00:28:02,993 --> 00:28:06,327
CHEN: Oh, you like fine ladies?
You want honey girls?

343
00:28:06,362 --> 00:28:08,066
MATT: "Fine ladies"? (SCOFFS)
PETE: "Fine ladies..."

344
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:09,167
MATT: Filthy whores, is more like it.

345
00:28:09,201 --> 00:28:11,168
(ALL CHATTERING)

346
00:28:13,203 --> 00:28:16,508
- Is this Chang's place?
- What kind of a slut shop is this anyway?

347
00:28:16,543 --> 00:28:19,343
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

348
00:28:19,911 --> 00:28:21,846
Gentlemen. Gentlemen.

349
00:28:24,688 --> 00:28:27,489
Is there a problem? Surely we
have something to soothe you.

350
00:28:27,924 --> 00:28:29,690
(CHUCKLES MOCKINGLY)

351
00:28:29,725 --> 00:28:32,726
We got a fancy one here, boys.

352
00:28:32,760 --> 00:28:35,461
This yellow monkey's
speakin' the king's English.

353
00:28:35,496 --> 00:28:37,296
Perhaps one of our pleasure-ladies?

354
00:28:37,330 --> 00:28:39,030
I wouldn't put my finger in 'em.

355
00:28:39,698 --> 00:28:41,699
A pipe of dreams, then?
There will be no charge.

356
00:28:41,734 --> 00:28:43,468
No, we don't want your charity.

357
00:28:43,768 --> 00:28:46,643
Hmm. Then there is no way we can help you.

358
00:28:46,646 --> 00:28:47,672
Sorry to say.

359
00:28:48,272 --> 00:28:50,720
Go ahead then. Throw us out.

360
00:28:50,820 --> 00:28:52,642
See how that goes for you, Jake.

361
00:28:53,709 --> 00:28:55,344
My name is Chang.

362
00:28:56,879 --> 00:28:57,879
- Hey!
- (GRUNTS)

363
00:29:05,955 --> 00:29:07,288
(SCREAMS)

364
00:29:16,869 --> 00:29:18,536
Now march, Jake.

365
00:29:24,875 --> 00:29:27,309
Chop, chop. You think
you're better than us?

366
00:29:27,344 --> 00:29:29,946
Yeah, he does, you know.
We'll show him who's better.

367
00:29:29,980 --> 00:29:31,014
Move!

368
00:29:32,881 --> 00:29:34,449
(SCREAMING)

369
00:29:35,751 --> 00:29:36,750
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

370
00:29:42,093 --> 00:29:43,093
(MEN CHUCKLING)

371
00:29:48,401 --> 00:29:51,272
Where's them fancy English
words now, Chinaman?

372
00:30:00,719 --> 00:30:02,487
Get them ropes.

373
00:30:03,189 --> 00:30:05,388
(INDISTINCT CHATTER IN CANTONESE)

374
00:30:05,688 --> 00:30:06,687
Do it!

375
00:30:11,427 --> 00:30:12,695
That'll do.

376
00:30:17,633 --> 00:30:20,300
_

377
00:30:20,435 --> 00:30:21,769
What's that you're sayin'?

378
00:30:21,970 --> 00:30:25,706
I said it would be best for you to kill me.
Now that you've begun.

379
00:30:26,758 --> 00:30:28,228
(GRUNTS)

380
00:30:40,910 --> 00:30:43,747
Pray you do not live long enough
to change places with him.

381
00:30:43,782 --> 00:30:44,815
(LAUGHS)

382
00:30:47,918 --> 00:30:51,653
Get back to your tents! Go on, get back!

383
00:30:53,523 --> 00:30:55,125
Go on, get out of it!

384
00:30:59,959 --> 00:31:00,959
Pull him up!

385
00:31:01,227 --> 00:31:03,063
(GRUNTING)

386
00:31:12,302 --> 00:31:13,500
- Come on.
- (PETE LAUGHS)

387
00:31:13,535 --> 00:31:15,169
Come on, let's go. Move.

388
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:31,753
Trouble! Chang!

389
00:31:36,861 --> 00:31:38,830
(GASPING)

390
00:31:50,739 --> 00:31:52,439
(SPEAKS CANTONESE)

391
00:31:59,713 --> 00:32:01,045
(GRUNTS)

392
00:32:09,623 --> 00:32:10,623
(GASPING)

393
00:32:11,726 --> 00:32:13,428
(COUGHING)

394
00:32:32,713 --> 00:32:34,014
(PANTING)

395
00:32:45,130 --> 00:32:46,897
(PLAYING HARMONICA)

396
00:32:57,246 --> 00:32:59,514
Oh, I was right, then.

397
00:33:00,250 --> 00:33:03,554
You have found some grievous error of mine.

398
00:33:03,756 --> 00:33:05,789
- I found an error, all right.
- Mmm.

399
00:33:08,358 --> 00:33:10,124
But it wasn't yours.

400
00:33:12,861 --> 00:33:14,593
Salt Lake City?

401
00:33:16,595 --> 00:33:17,595
My father.

402
00:33:19,330 --> 00:33:21,330
No. No, it can't be.

403
00:33:21,364 --> 00:33:25,999
My father, The Lion of the
Lord, Brother Brigham...

404
00:33:26,034 --> 00:33:29,067
- (THE SWEDE EXCLAIMS)
- the Prophet, the deliverer of his people,

405
00:33:30,070 --> 00:33:34,042
a liar, a thief, a cheat.

406
00:33:34,076 --> 00:33:36,547
Boy, you must not utter such blasphemy.

407
00:33:36,581 --> 00:33:38,714
He has cheated me

408
00:33:39,683 --> 00:33:41,184
since the moment that we got here!

409
00:33:41,218 --> 00:33:42,919
Is that not what those books of yours say?

410
00:33:42,954 --> 00:33:44,121
Uh, I...

411
00:33:44,456 --> 00:33:45,989
Is it or isn't it?

412
00:33:47,557 --> 00:33:48,624
Yes.

413
00:33:49,060 --> 00:33:54,868
But I'm sure there is a viable explanation.

414
00:33:54,902 --> 00:33:56,437
Damn you, man.

415
00:34:14,327 --> 00:34:15,861
I want justice.

416
00:34:16,497 --> 00:34:17,665
(COUGHING)

417
00:34:23,073 --> 00:34:25,476
It's not easy to know what that means.

418
00:34:27,679 --> 00:34:30,746
And frankly, Mr. Chang, I...
I'm not sure what's possible.

419
00:34:31,582 --> 00:34:33,083
What's possible?

420
00:34:45,127 --> 00:34:46,729
(CHANG COUGHING)

421
00:34:56,673 --> 00:35:00,615
A 20-year-old Chinaman gets on
a boat in Guangdong, China.

422
00:35:01,182 --> 00:35:04,988
He sets sail with a Sze Yup Company
flyer and a ticket for passage.

423
00:35:05,423 --> 00:35:08,162
He arrives in San Francisco,
where a team of men herd him

424
00:35:08,197 --> 00:35:12,534
and a hundred others into freight
cars that transport them to Cisco.

425
00:35:12,969 --> 00:35:17,472
In Cisco, another team
loads the men into wagons.

426
00:35:17,507 --> 00:35:21,106
Then three days later, after
traversing the Sierra Summit,

427
00:35:22,074 --> 00:35:24,976
they deliver those
Chinamen to the railroad.

428
00:35:25,978 --> 00:35:28,444
Now neither you, you

429
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:34,636
or you has the capability to
reproduce that impossible feat once,

430
00:35:34,903 --> 00:35:37,805
let alone 15,000 times.

431
00:35:38,206 --> 00:35:42,077
So when I ask for justice, I mean justice.

432
00:35:43,780 --> 00:35:45,780
The kind reserved for civilized men,

433
00:35:47,448 --> 00:35:49,584
free from the danger of a rope.

434
00:35:56,509 --> 00:36:00,080
Well, Mr. Chang, I'll tell you.

435
00:36:00,649 --> 00:36:03,517
Now, what justice means in
America is, we have a trial.

436
00:36:03,551 --> 00:36:05,552
You want justice, that's it.

437
00:36:05,586 --> 00:36:08,491
COLLIS: We don't go hanging people
in this country without a trial.

438
00:36:08,526 --> 00:36:13,229
What we are, as you have pointed
out, a civilized nation after all.

439
00:36:20,208 --> 00:36:21,608
A trial, then.

440
00:36:34,150 --> 00:36:35,617
(DOOR CLOSES)

441
00:36:47,660 --> 00:36:52,130
He's no ordinary Chinaman. He's our one
and only provider of Chinese workers.

442
00:36:52,164 --> 00:36:54,864
And we must be perceived
to do right by him.

443
00:36:56,199 --> 00:36:58,835
I count on you two to keep
control of these things.

444
00:36:58,869 --> 00:37:01,304
I mean, need I remind you,
there's 12,000 Chinese sleeping,

445
00:37:01,338 --> 00:37:02,840
not 100 yards from here.

446
00:37:02,874 --> 00:37:04,343
Well, if they see us walking a man

447
00:37:04,377 --> 00:37:06,145
after they strung up one of their own?

448
00:37:06,179 --> 00:37:08,612
A judge and jury's never
gonna convict those men.

449
00:37:08,646 --> 00:37:10,779
We promised him a trial.

450
00:37:10,814 --> 00:37:12,581
You need to telegram Stanford.

451
00:37:13,016 --> 00:37:14,978
My son-of-a-bitch partner?

452
00:37:15,013 --> 00:37:17,043
I'd rather feed my scrotum
to a grinder monkey.

453
00:37:17,343 --> 00:37:20,675
He's a lawyer. He can serve as a judge.
Impanel a jury.

454
00:37:22,442 --> 00:37:24,743
God damn it, you're right. (SIGHS)

455
00:37:27,582 --> 00:37:29,182
You come with me.

456
00:37:33,557 --> 00:37:35,558
- Where are we goin'?
- To arrest them men.

457
00:37:36,026 --> 00:37:37,388
- Arrest them?
- It's for their own good.

458
00:37:37,391 --> 00:37:38,396
They ain't safe walkin' around.

459
00:37:38,428 --> 00:37:40,297
Whose side are you on, anyway?

460
00:37:40,331 --> 00:37:41,366
(CULLEN GRUNTS)

461
00:37:49,210 --> 00:37:50,478
(SPITS)

462
00:37:50,512 --> 00:37:52,013
You get that outta your system?

463
00:37:54,784 --> 00:37:55,785
(SIGHS)

464
00:37:56,988 --> 00:37:59,458
Same side as you. The railroad's.

465
00:38:03,895 --> 00:38:05,096
Now let's go.

466
00:38:13,972 --> 00:38:16,444
Stand up. You're under arrest.

467
00:38:17,079 --> 00:38:19,380
- Arrest? For what?
- Murder. Stand up.

468
00:38:20,449 --> 00:38:22,352
- Stro, come on.
- Stand up.

469
00:38:22,820 --> 00:38:24,854
- MATT: They were Chinamen.
- JAMES: Yeah.

470
00:38:25,589 --> 00:38:27,258
The wrong Chinamen.

471
00:38:32,193 --> 00:38:33,193
Up.

472
00:38:34,429 --> 00:38:35,763
(GROANING)

473
00:38:36,231 --> 00:38:38,329
When you read this, Father,

474
00:38:39,797 --> 00:38:42,933
you'll say, "Phineas is whining
and complaining again."

475
00:38:43,302 --> 00:38:46,405
You'll say that you should
have sent one of my brothers.

476
00:38:47,374 --> 00:38:52,250
You've never trusted me and now you
have set me an impossible task,

477
00:38:52,818 --> 00:38:55,517
in wild and miserable country,

478
00:38:56,086 --> 00:38:59,854
and have cheated me of the
money I need to succeed.

479
00:39:00,590 --> 00:39:03,693
You've made sure that I'd fail, always.

480
00:39:04,596 --> 00:39:06,298
But this time, I have the proof.

481
00:39:06,332 --> 00:39:07,967
Stop, stop.

482
00:39:08,002 --> 00:39:12,473
You must not do this. You must not.

483
00:39:12,841 --> 00:39:18,110
To address the Lord's servant in this
way, His sainted presence on earth...

484
00:39:18,144 --> 00:39:20,680
By "whom," you mean my
cruel, unjust father?

485
00:39:20,714 --> 00:39:22,015
Please, Brother.

486
00:39:22,050 --> 00:39:24,420
Who has ignored me my whole life?

487
00:39:24,621 --> 00:39:26,754
Who has undermined my every effort?

488
00:39:26,788 --> 00:39:29,753
Control yourself.

489
00:39:31,824 --> 00:39:33,494
For your own good.

490
00:39:33,995 --> 00:39:36,495
Let me have that, and go.

491
00:39:48,210 --> 00:39:49,709
One of my brothers.

492
00:39:51,444 --> 00:39:53,313
- You don't understand.
- Shh.

493
00:39:56,119 --> 00:40:01,857
Have you asked yourself what...
What will be the consequence of...

494
00:40:01,891 --> 00:40:03,456
Of this letter?

495
00:40:06,462 --> 00:40:11,936
- I have...
- You have said what is in your heart,

496
00:40:13,473 --> 00:40:14,941
and what is true.

497
00:40:16,244 --> 00:40:20,576
But truth... Truth does
not always serve us.

498
00:40:21,711 --> 00:40:22,912
When it is...

499
00:40:23,881 --> 00:40:27,618
When it is so naked and hot,

